('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'preheat', 'Recipes often instruct to preheat ovens before baking. What does the prefix \"pre-\" in \"preheat\" indicate?', 'Before', 'After', 'During', 'Beyond', 'The prefix \"pre-\" means \"before\", indicating an action done beforehand.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'discontinue', 'The company will discontinue this product line next year. What does the prefix \"dis-\" in \"discontinue\" mean?', 'Reverse', 'Support', 'Improve', 'Create', 'The prefix \"dis-\" indicates reversal or cessation of an action.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'illogical', 'The argument was dismissed as illogical. What does the prefix \"il-\" in \"illogical\" mean?', 'Not', 'Very', 'Beyond', 'Similar', 'The prefix \"il-\" (a form of \"in-\") means \"not\", creating a negative meaning.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'misinterpret', 'Cultural differences can cause people to misinterpret gestures. What does the prefix \"mis-\" in \"misinterpret\" mean?', 'Incorrectly', 'Correctly', 'Overly', 'Under', 'The prefix \"mis-\" means \"wrongly\" or \"badly\", indicating error.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'substandard', 'Inspectors rejected the substandard materials. What does the prefix \"sub-\" in \"substandard\" mean?', 'Below', 'Above', 'Equal', 'Beyond', 'The prefix \"sub-\" means \"under\" or \"below\", denoting inferior quality.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'overestimate', 'Many overestimate their initial project timelines. What does the prefix \"over-\" in \"overestimate\" mean?', 'Excessively', 'Insufficiently', 'Precisely', 'Rarely', 'The prefix \"over-\" means \"too much\", implying excess.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'autobiography', 'Her autobiography details her early career struggles. What does the prefix \"auto-\" in \"autobiography\" mean?', 'Self', 'Life', 'Time', 'Book', 'The prefix \"auto-\" means \"self\", indicating something done by oneself.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'bilingual', 'Job candidates often benefit from being bilingual. What does the prefix \"bi-\" in \"bilingual\" mean?', 'Two', 'Many', 'Single', 'Partial', 'The prefix \"bi-\" means \"two\", referring to dual capability.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'postpone', 'The meeting will postpone until next week. What does the prefix \"post-\" in \"postpone\" mean?', 'After', 'Before', 'During', 'Against', 'The prefix \"post-\" means \"after\", indicating a delayed action.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'forewarn', 'Meteorologists forewarn citizens about storms. What does the prefix \"fore-\" in \"forewarn\" mean?', 'Ahead', 'Behind', 'During', 'After', 'The prefix \"fore-\" means \"before\" or \"in advance\", suggesting prior action.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'interconnected', 'Ecosystems are highly interconnected. What does the prefix \"inter-\" in \"interconnected\" mean?', 'Between', 'Within', 'Against', 'After', 'The prefix \"inter-\" means \"between\" or \"among\", denoting mutual relationships.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'transatlantic', 'Transatlantic flights connect New York and London. What does the prefix \"trans-\" in \"transatlantic\" mean?', 'Across', 'Under', 'Against', 'Within', 'The prefix \"trans-\" means \"across\" or \"beyond\", indicating crossing boundaries.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'supervisor', 'Report any issues to your supervisor immediately. What does the prefix \"super-\" in \"supervisor\" mean?', 'Over', 'Under', 'Equal', 'Against', 'The prefix \"super-\" means \"above\" or \"beyond\", implying higher authority.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'semiconscious', 'The injured driver was semiconscious at the scene. What does the prefix \"semi-\" in \"semiconscious\" mean?', 'Partial', 'Complete', 'Against', 'Beyond', 'The prefix \"semi-\" means \"half\" or \"partially\", indicating incompleteness.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'microscope', 'Scientists use microscopes to study cells. What does the prefix \"micro-\" in \"microscope\" mean?', 'Small', 'Large', 'Distant', 'Multiple', 'The prefix \"micro-\" means \"very small\", referring to tiny-scale observation.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'macroeconomic', 'Governments monitor macroeconomic indicators. What does the prefix \"macro-\" in \"macroeconomic\" mean?', 'Large-scale', 'Small-scale', 'Internal', 'Temporary', 'The prefix \"macro-\" means \"large\", indicating broad system analysis.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'monotone', 'His monotone delivery made the lecture tedious. What does the prefix \"mono-\" in \"monotone\" mean?', 'Single', 'Multiple', 'Changing', 'Loud', 'The prefix \"mono-\" means \"one\" or \"single\", denoting uniformity.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'multicultural', 'Toronto is known for its multicultural neighborhoods. What does the prefix \"multi-\" in \"multicultural\" mean?', 'Many', 'Single', 'Dual', 'Specific', 'The prefix \"multi-\" means \"many\", indicating diversity.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'centimeter', 'A centimeter is a unit of measurement. What does the prefix \"centi-\" in \"centimeter\" mean?', 'Hundredth', 'Thousandth', 'Tenth', 'Millionth', 'The prefix \"centi-\" means \"hundredth\", denoting fraction (1/100).'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'kilometer', 'The race was five kilometers long. What does the prefix \"kilo-\" in \"kilometer\" mean?', 'Thousand', 'Hundred', 'Million', 'Tenth', 'The prefix \"kilo-\" means \"thousand\", indicating multiplication (x1000).'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'darkness', 'The darkness made navigation difficult. What does the suffix \"-ness\" in \"darkness\" express?', 'State', 'Process', 'Diminish', 'Quality', 'The suffix \"-ness\" turns adjectives into nouns indicating a state or condition.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'flexible', 'Rubber is highly flexible material. What does the suffix \"-ible\" in \"flexible\" indicate?', 'Capable of', 'Full of', 'Without', 'State of', 'The suffix \"-ible\" means \"capable of being\", showing adaptability.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'childish', 'His childish behavior annoyed the team. What does the suffix \"-ish\" in \"childish\" mean?', 'Resembling', 'Without', 'Full of', 'State of', 'The suffix \"-ish\" means \"having the characteristics of\", implying immaturity.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'happiness', 'True happiness comes from within. What does the suffix \"-ness\" in \"happiness\" express?', 'State of being', 'Action', 'Reduction', 'Capability', 'The suffix \"-ness\" forms nouns indicating a quality or state.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'reliant', 'Babies are reliant on caregivers. What does the suffix \"-ant\" in \"reliant\" indicate?', 'Inclined to', 'Without', 'Formerly', 'Overly', 'The suffix \"-ant\" means \"inclined to\" or \"performing\", showing dependence.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'countless', 'There are countless stars in the universe. What does the suffix \"-less\" in \"countless\" mean?', 'Without', 'Full of', 'Capable of', 'State of', 'The suffix \"-less\" means \"lacking\" or \"without\", denoting absence.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'quickness', 'Cheetahs are known for their quickness. What does the suffix \"-ness\" in \"quickness\" express?', 'Quality', 'Process', 'Diminution', 'Location', 'The suffix \"-ness\" turns adjectives into nouns denoting a quality.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'joyful', 'Children\'s laughter is joyful. What does the suffix \"-ful\" in \"joyful\" mean?', 'Full of', 'Without', 'Capable of', 'State of', 'The suffix \"-ful\" means \"full of\" or \"characterized by\", indicating abundance.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'slowly', 'She walked slowly due to injury. What does the suffix \"-ly\" in \"slowly\" indicate?', 'Manner', 'State', 'Capability', 'Time', 'The suffix \"-ly\" turns adjectives into adverbs describing manner.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'teacher', 'The teacher explained the concept clearly. What does the suffix \"-er\" in \"teacher\" mean?', 'One who does', 'State of', 'Without', 'Process', 'The suffix \"-er\" indicates a person performing an action.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'freedom', 'Citizens value their freedom. What does the suffix \"-dom\" in \"freedom\" express?', 'Condition', 'Place', 'Small version', 'Action', 'The suffix \"-dom\" forms nouns indicating a state or condition.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'bakery', 'We bought bread at the bakery. What does the suffix \"-ery\" in \"bakery\" indicate?', 'Place of', 'State of', 'Without', 'Capable of', 'The suffix \"-ery\" means \"place where an activity occurs\".'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'dentist', 'Visit your dentist twice a year. What does the suffix \"-ist\" in \"dentist\" mean?', 'Practitioner', 'Place', 'State', 'Process', 'The suffix \"-ist\" denotes a person specializing in a field.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'laughable', 'His excuse was laughable. What does the suffix \"-able\" in \"laughable\" indicate?', 'Capable of', 'Full of', 'Without', 'Quality', 'The suffix \"-able\" means \"worthy of\" or \"capable of being\", suggesting susceptibility.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'government', 'The government announced new policies. What does the suffix \"-ment\" in \"government\" express?', 'Result of', 'State of', 'Capability', 'Without', 'The suffix \"-ment\" forms nouns indicating an action or resulting state.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'friendship', 'Their friendship lasted decades. What does the suffix \"-ship\" in \"friendship\" mean?', 'State of', 'Place', 'Action', 'Small', 'The suffix \"-ship\" denotes a state, condition, or quality.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'violinist', 'The violinist performed brilliantly. What does the suffix \"-ist\" in \"violinist\" indicate?', 'Specialist', 'Place', 'State', 'Action', 'The suffix \"-ist\" refers to a person who practices something.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'homesick', 'Travelers often feel homesick abroad. What does the suffix \"-sick\" in \"homesick\" mean?', 'Longing for', 'Cured of', 'Full of', 'Without', 'The suffix \"-sick\" means \"afflicted with longing for\", denoting yearning.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'employee', 'Every employee received a bonus. What does the suffix \"-ee\" in \"employee\" mean?', 'Recipient', 'Doer', 'Place', 'State', 'The suffix \"-ee\" indicates a person who receives an action.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'wisdom', 'Grandparents share wisdom with grandchildren. What does the suffix \"-dom\" in \"wisdom\" express?', 'Condition', 'Action', 'Capability', 'Small', 'The suffix \"-dom\" forms abstract nouns indicating a state.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'greenish', 'The pond had a greenish tint. What does the suffix \"-ish\" in \"greenish\" mean?', 'Somewhat', 'Completely', 'Without', 'Overly', 'The suffix \"-ish\" means \"somewhat\" or \"resembling\", indicating approximation.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'excitement', 'The excitement before the concert was palpable. What does the suffix \"-ment\" in \"excitement\" indicate?', 'State/Result', 'Capability', 'Place', 'Diminution', 'The suffix \"-ment\" forms nouns denoting a condition or product of an action.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'endless', 'The desert seemed endless. What does the suffix \"-less\" in \"endless\" mean?', 'Without', 'Full of', 'Capable of', 'State of', 'The suffix \"-less\" means \"lacking\", implying boundlessness.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'actor', 'The actor memorized his lines. What does the suffix \"-or\" in \"actor\" mean?', 'Person who', 'Place where', 'State of', 'Process', 'The suffix \"-or\" indicates a person performing a specific action.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'sensitive', 'Be sensitive to others\' feelings. What does the suffix \"-ive\" in \"sensitive\" indicate?', 'Tending to', 'Without', 'Full of', 'Capable of', 'The suffix \"-ive\" means \"having the nature of\", showing inclination.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'lately', 'She has been busy lately. What does the suffix \"-ly\" in \"lately\" express?', 'Time', 'Manner', 'Place', 'State', 'The suffix \"-ly\" forms adverbs indicating time-related modification.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'dangerous', 'Ice roads are dangerous in spring. What does the suffix \"-ous\" in \"dangerous\" mean?', 'Full of', 'Without', 'Capable of', 'State of', 'The suffix \"-ous\" means \"full of\" or \"having\", denoting hazard.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'happiness', 'Family gatherings bring happiness. What does the suffix \"-ness\" in \"happiness\" express?', 'State', 'Action', 'Location', 'Agent', 'The suffix \"-ness\" creates abstract nouns indicating a condition.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'biology', 'Biology studies living organisms. What does the suffix \"-logy\" in \"biology\" mean?', 'Study of', 'Love of', 'State of', 'Without', 'The suffix \"-logy\" means \"study of\" or \"science of\", denoting a discipline.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'fearless', 'Firefighters are fearless heroes. What does the suffix \"-less\" in \"fearless\" indicate?', 'Lacking', 'Full of', 'Capable of', 'State of', 'The suffix \"-less\" means \"without\", showing absence of fear.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'employee', 'The employee completed the training. What does the suffix \"-ee\" in \"employee\" mean?', 'Recipient', 'Doer', 'Place', 'Action', 'The suffix \"-ee\" denotes a person who receives the action.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'benevolent', 'The benevolent donor anonymously funded scholarships. What does \"bene-\" mean?', 'Good', 'Evil', 'Small', 'After', '\"bene-\" means \"good\" (Latin origin), seen in beneficial/benediction'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'contradict', 'Witnesses may contradict previous statements under oath. What does \"contra-\" mean?', 'Against', 'Support', 'Before', 'Alongside', '\"contra-\" means \"against\" or \"opposite\", as in contrast/contrary'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'extraterrestrial', 'Scientists search for extraterrestrial life. What does \"extra-\" mean?', 'Beyond', 'Within', 'Below', 'Against', '\"extra-\" means \"outside/beyond\", like extraordinary/extracurricular'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'hyperactive', 'Hyperactive children need specialized support. What does \"hyper-\" mean?', 'Excessive', 'Insufficient', 'Normal', 'Under', '\"hyper-\" denotes excess (Greek: huper = over), opposite of \"hypo-\"'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'neonatal', 'Neonatal care units save premature infants. What does \"neo-\" mean?', 'New', 'Old', 'Against', 'Same', '\"neo-\" means \"new/recent\" (Greek: neos), as in neolithic/neophyte'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'orthodontist', 'Orthodontists correct dental misalignments. What does \"ortho-\" mean?', 'Straight', 'Crooked', 'Tooth', 'Painful', '\"ortho-\" means \"correct/straight\" (Greek: orthos), like orthopedics/orthography'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'panorama', 'The mountain panorama took our breath away. What does \"pan-\" mean?', 'All', 'Partial', 'Against', 'Small', '\"pan-\" means \"all-encompassing\" (Greek: pan), as in pandemic/panacea'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'prototype', 'Engineers tested the prototype extensively. What does \"proto-\" mean?', 'First', 'Last', 'Flawed', 'Temporary', '\"proto-\" means \"original/first\" (Greek: protos), like protocol/protostar'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'retroactive', 'The law had retroactive effects. What does \"retro-\" mean?', 'Backward', 'Forward', 'Neutral', 'Accelerated', '\"retro-\" means \"backward\" (Latin: retro), as in retrograde/retrospect'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'triennial', 'Triennial reviews assess long-term progress. What does \"tri-\" mean?', 'Three', 'Four', 'Yearly', 'Half', '\"tri-\" denotes three (Latin: tres), like triangle/tricycle'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'ultramodern', 'The ultramodern design used futuristic materials. What does \"ultra-\" mean?', 'Extreme', 'Moderate', 'Outdated', 'Minimal', '\"ultra-\" means \"beyond/extreme\" (Latin: ultra), as in ultraviolet/ultrasound'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'underdeveloped', 'Underdeveloped regions lack infrastructure. What does \"under-\" mean?', 'Insufficient', 'Excessive', 'Optimal', 'Temporary', '\"under-\" indicates deficiency or beneath, opposite of \"over-\"'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'hemisphere', 'The Southern Hemisphere experiences winter in July. What does \"hemi-\" mean?', 'Half', 'Whole', 'Double', 'Equal', '\"hemi-\" means half (Greek: hemi), as in hemicycle/hemiplegia'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'readable', 'The document must be readable for all audiences. What does \"-able\" indicate?', 'Capable of', 'Full of', 'Without', 'Process', '\"-able\" means \"capable of being\" (readable = can be read)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'gardener', 'The gardener pruned the rose bushes. What does \"-er\" mean?', 'One who does', 'Place for', 'State of', 'Small version', '\"-er\" denotes a person performing an action (teach → teacher)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'sleepless', 'Sleepless nights affected her focus. What does \"-less\" mean?', 'Without', 'Full of', 'Characterized by', 'Process', '\"-less\" indicates absence (sleepless = without sleep)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'happiness', 'True happiness comes from within. What does \"-ness\" express?', 'State of being', 'Action', 'Capability', 'Reduction', '\"-ness\" creates nouns from adjectives (happy → happiness)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'quarrelsome', 'The quarrelsome neighbor argued daily. What does \"-some\" mean?', 'Tending to', 'Without', 'Full of', 'Place', '\"-some\" means \"characterized by\" (burden → burdensome)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'modernize', 'Companies must modernize to compete. What does \"-ize\" mean?', 'To make', 'State of', 'Without', 'Small', '\"-ize\" means \"to cause to be\" (modern → modernize)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'kindred', 'They felt a kindred connection instantly. What does \"-red\" mean?', 'State/condition', 'Action', 'Place', 'Diminutive', '\"-red\" is a rare suffix denoting state (hatred/kindred)');
