('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'freedom', 'Freedom requires responsibility. What does \"-dom\" express?', 'Condition of', 'Place', 'Action', 'Small', '\"-dom\" indicates state or realm (king → kingdom)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'bakery', 'The bakery sold artisan breads. What does \"-ery\" mean?', 'Place of', 'State', 'Action', 'Collective', '\"-ery\" denotes location or activity (bake → bakery)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'feminism', 'Modern feminism addresses intersectionality. What does \"-ism\" mean?', 'Doctrine', 'Agent', 'State', 'Process', '\"-ism\" denotes belief systems (capital → capitalism)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'eatery', 'The new eatery specialized in vegan cuisine. What does \"-ery\" indicate?', 'Place', 'Doctrine', 'State', 'Small', 'Alternative \"-ery\" usage (eat → eatery = eating place)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'diction', 'The actor\'s diction was exceptionally clear. What does \"-tion\" mean?', 'Action/result', 'State', 'Agent', 'Small', '\"-tion\" forms nouns from verbs (dictate → diction)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'childhood', 'Her childhood memories were vivid. What does \"-hood\" express?', 'State/period', 'Place', 'Action', 'Quality', '\"-hood\" indicates life stage (mother → motherhood)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'criticize', 'Critics often criticize experimental art. What does \"-ize\" indicate?', 'To perform action', 'State of', 'Without', 'Place', '\"-ize\" forms verbs (critic → criticize = to critique)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'greenish', 'The walls were painted greenish blue. What does \"-ish\" mean?', 'Somewhat', 'Completely', 'Without', 'Extremely', '\"-ish\" means \"having qualities of\" (green → greenish)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'ambidextrous', 'Ambidextrous athletes have competitive advantages. What does \"ambi-\" mean?', 'Both', 'One', 'Left', 'Right', '\"ambi-\" means \"both\" (Latin: ambi), seen in ambiguous/ambivalence'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'antechamber', 'Guests waited in the antechamber before the meeting. What does \"ante-\" mean?', 'Before', 'After', 'Against', 'Within', '\"ante-\" means \"preceding\" (Latin: ante), as in antecedent/antedate'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'antidote', 'Doctors administered the antidote immediately. What does \"anti-\" mean?', 'Against', 'Supporting', 'Similar', 'Enhancing', '\"anti-\" means \"counteracting\" (Greek: anti), like antibiotic/antifreeze'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'coauthor', 'They decided to coauthor the research paper. What does \"co-\" mean?', 'Jointly', 'Against', 'Former', 'Lead', '\"co-\" means \"together\" (Latin: cum), as in cooperate/coexist'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'demagnetize', 'Technicians demagnetize credit cards accidentally exposed to magnets. What does \"de-\" mean?', 'Remove', 'Add', 'Strengthen', 'Measure', '\"de-\" indicates reversal (magnetize → demagnetize)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'dysfunctional', 'The dysfunctional system caused frequent errors. What does \"dys-\" mean?', 'Faulty', 'Highly', 'New', 'Simple', '\"dys-\" means \"bad/difficult\" (Greek: dus), as in dyslexia/dystopia'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'excommunicate', 'The church could excommunicate heretics. What does \"ex-\" mean?', 'Out', 'In', 'Former', 'Against', '\"ex-\" means \"out of\" (Latin: ex), seen in expel/exhale'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'foreground', 'The artist emphasized foreground elements. What does \"fore-\" mean?', 'Front', 'Back', 'Middle', 'Side', '\"fore-\" means \"ahead/in front\" (Old English), as in forehead/foreword'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'heterogeneous', 'The heterogeneous group included diverse perspectives. What does \"hetero-\" mean?', 'Different', 'Same', 'Mixed', 'Strange', '\"hetero-\" means \"other\" (Greek: heteros), like heterosexual/heterodox'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'hypodermic', 'Nurses use hypodermic needles for injections. What does \"hypo-\" mean?', 'Under', 'Over', 'Between', 'Against', '\"hypo-\" means \"beneath\" (Greek: hypo), as in hypothesis/hypothermia'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'intrastate', 'Intrastate commerce follows state regulations. What does \"intra-\" mean?', 'Within', 'Between', 'Against', 'Beyond', '\"intra-\" means \"inside\" (Latin: intra), like intravenous/intramural'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'nonentity', 'The critic dismissed him as a nonentity. What does \"non-\" mean?', 'Not', 'Former', 'Partial', 'Overly', '\"non-\" indicates negation (entity → nonentity = unimportant thing)'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Word Formation', 'perforate', 'The machine perforates paper for easy tearing. What does \"per-\" mean?', 'Through', 'Around', 'Against', 'Before', '\"per-\" means \"completely\" (Latin: per), as in permeate/perceive'),
